<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-03-22T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-03-22T20:00:00-05:00" n="527" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d527">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13417: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-23T09:00:00+08:00">March 23, 1936—9
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received March 22—11:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>145. Embassy’s 144, March 22, 4 p.m. Misses Hamilton, Cade and Cheny
                            arrived in Peiping last night.</p>
                        <p>This telegram and Embassy’s 144, March 22, 4 p.m. have been repeated to
                            Nanking and Shanghai.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>